name: Ceiling & Cabinet Fans
description: S&P's range of Ceiling and Wall Mounted Centrifugal Exhaust fans primarily exhaust air from bathrooms in residential and commercial settings.

series.name: Ceiling Mount Ventilator
series.description: Incredibly reliable. Unbelievably quiet. Offering the CFM choices you need at the lowest sound levels in the industry.

series.name: Cabinet Ventilator
series.description: Incredibly reliable. Unbelievably quiet. Offering the CFM choices you need at the lowest sound levels in the industry.

name: Centrifugal Filtered Supply Fans
description: Centrifugal Filtered Supply fans provide make-up air to commercial or industrial applications.

series.name: KSFV
series.description: The KSFV fans are roof curb or curb cap mounted filtered supply fans rated from 475 to over 12,600 CFM, with static pressure capabilities to 2-1/2". They are specifically designed for non-tempered, filtered make-up air in kitchen hood applications.

series.name: CSF
series.description: Centrifugal Filtered Supply Fans units are roof mounted filtered supply fans rated from 475 to over 12,500 CFM, with static pressure capability up to 2". CSF's rugged, heavy-gauge galvanized hood and stack provide maximum weather protection and long life.

series.name: LSF
series.description: Louver Filtered Supply Fans units are roof mounted filtered supply fans rated from 475 to over 12,500 CFM, with static pressure capabilities to 2". LSF's architecturally pleasing; heavy-gauge aluminum louver design provides long life and the utmost in performance efficiency.

name: Centrifugal Roof & Wall Fans
description: Centrifugal Roof and Wall fans are installed on a roof curb or exterior wall. These types of fans are used to exhaust and/or supply air in commercial or institutional buildings.

series.name: SDBD and SDBDe
series.description: SDBD and SDBDe direct drive fans are designed to exhaust air up to 4,984 CFM, with high static pressure capability up to 2-1/4". The non-overloading backward inclined wheel with its higher static pressure capability makes these units suitable for either ducted or non-ducted applications.

series.name: SDB
series.description: The SDB, with its sleek spun aluminum exterior and efficient design, ensures optimal performance at high static pressures. Easy adjustments via belt drives and reliability are guaranteed with AMCA Air and Sound and cULus 705 certifications.

series.name: STXD
series.description: The Model STXD direct drive fans, featuring attractive aluminum exteriors, efficiently exhaust air in high-pressure environments up to 4,780 CFM. These fans are versatile, suitable for both ducted and nonducted applications, and promise quiet, low-maintenance operation with no belts or fan bearings to maintain.

series.name: STXB
series.description: STXB and STXB-RHUL Upblast Belt Drive Centrifugal Roof/Sidewall Exhaust Fans are designed to exhaust air up to 37,290 CFM in high static pressure applications to 3". The aluminum exterior provides an attractive appearance. Belt drive results in lower operating RPM and sound levels, making the Series STXB well suited to applications where quiet operation is important.

series.name: LPD and LPD-SF
series.description: The LPD and LPD-SF are sleek, versatile direct drive fans, designed to exhaust air efficiently in areas requiring low CFM up to 420 with high static pressure. These are ideal for various ventilations like bathrooms or offices and offer flexible mounting options; LPD is optimal for curb mounting and LPD-SF has a self-flashing base for roof or sidewall mounting.

series.name: CWD
series.description: The Centrifugal Wall Mounted Exhauster Direct Drive Fans (CWD) offer a sleek, low-profile design, efficiently exhausting up to 3,360 CFM. These corrosion-resistant units are perfect for sidewall mounting in spaces like offices or restaurants, ensuring quiet and minimal maintenance operation.

name: Energy Recovery Ventilators
description: Energy Recovery Ventilators supply and exhaust equal amounts of air creating a balanced system which is optimal for all applications.

series.name: TR
series.description: S&P's TR Series ensures optimal indoor air quality by efficiently exchanging stale air with fresh, using an advanced energy exchange core to maintain comfort and prevent contamination in all climates.

series.name: TRe
series.description: Total Recovery Premium, TRe, is the latest edition to S&P USA's line of Energy Recovery Ventilators. TRe can be used in any orientation and features an EC motor for great energy efficiency. Utilize TRe for any residential or light commercial project by individually balancing each airstream to account for variations of duct run lengths.

series.name: TRC
series.description: S&P's TRC Series efficiently refreshes indoor air in all climates, using an advanced energy exchange core to separate and prevent contamination between incoming and outgoing air streams, while transferring heat and humidity.

series.name: TRCeN
series.description: S&P's TRCe Series with EC Motor revitalizes indoor air by exchanging stale air for fresh in all climates, using an advanced "air-to-air" core to prevent contamination and efficiently transfer heat and humidity, ideal for commercial applications.

series.name: TRLPe
series.description: The Total Recovery series with EC Motor offers balanced energy ventilation through a multi-speed control and compact design, ideal for space-constrained residential and light commercial applications, ensuring efficient air-to-air energy exchange.

name: Gravity Vents
description: Gravity Vents are spun aluminum intake/relief ventilators designed for use in both gravity and mechanical ventilation systems.

series.name: RCXII
series.description: The sleek RCXII and RCXII-SF ventilators modulate air in enclosed spaces without a fan, available in sizes 6 to 36". RCXII mounts on a roof curb, and RCXII-SF installs under shingles without one, each including a standard galvanized birdscreen.

series.name: RLX
series.description: The RLX Aluminum Louvered Penthouse offers a sleek, modern solution for fresh air intake, pressure relief, and gravity applications. Customizable in size, it's ideal for hiding rooftop equipment and ensuring weather integrity with its storm-resistant design. Capacities range from 395 to 69,500 CFM, with larger custom options available. The companion louvered fan, Model LSF, ensures design consistency in rooftop installations.

series.name: BGH
series.description: BGH Gravity Ventilators offer a modern low silhouette design that blend with roof lines and other equipment. Designed for maximum airflow passage and weathertight integrity, BGH comes in either intake or relief models with aluminum or galvanized finishes. An extensive range of sizes is offered with many standard and optional features. Exhaust models have a 1:1 ratio of hood perimeter opening to throat area and supply models incorporate a 2:1 ratio.

name: High Volume Low Speed Fans
description: Tornado and Tempest High Volume Low Speed (THVLS) Series are specially designed to move greater quantities of air at lower operating speeds. These fans are equipped with wingtips to redirect outward airflow downward.

series.name: Tornado
series.description: Tornado HVLS is a 5-Blade High Volume Low-Speed fan model featuring a direct drive ECM, IP65 motor. This fan is equipped with wingtips to redirect outward airflow downward. Through the destratification process, the THVLS fan series will lower energy bills providing evaporative cooling effect in summer and allow for uniform temperature in winter

series.name: Tempest
series.description: Tempest HVLS is a 6-Blade High Volume Low-Speed fan model featuring a direct drive ECM, IP65 motor. This fan is equipped with wingtips to redirect outward airflow downward. Through the destratification process, the THVLS fan series will lower energy bills providing evaporative cooling effect in summer and allow for uniform temperature in winter.

name: In-line/Sidewall Duct Fans
description: Duct Mounted Mixed Flow In-line fans are used to exhaust, supply, or boost air through ductwork from one area to another in residential and commercial settings.

series.name: TD-MIXVENT
series.description: The TD-MIXVENT series is a compact in-line duct fan designed for maximum airflow and minimal noise, ideal for small to medium-sized ventilation installations requiring high airflow to pressure ratio in limited space environments like false ceiling voids and cabinets.

series.name: TD-SILENT
series.description: The TD-SILENT fans are ultra-quiet, low-profile units, constructed from durable reinforced plastic, featuring sound-absorbent insulation to dampen noise. Equipped with rubber gaskets on the inlet and outlet, they ensure easy installation, minimal vibrations, and an almost air-tight seal.

series.name: PV-DEDPV
series.description: The PV-DEDPV is a UL 705 listed Dryer Exhaust Duct Power Ventilator. It effectively helps residential clothes dryers overcome the high static pressure caused by long duct runs between the dryer and wall or roof cap.

series.name: PV-POWERVENT
series.description: The PV-POWERVENT series of direct drive centrifugal in-line duct ventilation fans consists of six model sizes 4", 5", 6", 8", 10 and 12.4" respectively. All models are designed for direct connection in-line with standard diameter round ducting. Airflow performance values range from 153 CFM (PV-100X) up to 943 CFM (PV-315X).

series.name: PRF
series.description: PRF fans, designed specifically for radon mitigation, have fully-sealed plastic housing and are capable of managing up to 1" of static pressure with backward inclined centrifugal blowers/motors. They fit easily with standard PVC couplings and feature large, accessible, watertight electrical boxes for hassle-free wiring.

series.name: SWF-SIDEWALL
series.description: The Sidewall Fan Series features powerful motors encased in an accessible outdoor-rated housing, ideal for spaces with limited indoor access. Available in sizes 4-8", they connect directly to standard ducting, with airflow ranging from 119 to 416 CFM.

series.name: SMXD
series.description: SMXD series is an direct drive mixed flow fan specially designed to maximize the airflow performance by acting as a hybrid between an axial and centrifugal fan. They produce a great amount of air while being able to handle higher pressures. It is more efficient and quieter than comparable tubular centrifugal fans. These fans can be used in exhaust, supply or return air applications.

series.name: SMXD-HT
series.description: SMXD series is an direct drive mixed flow fan specially designed to maximize the airflow performance by acting as a hybrid between an axial and centrifugal fan. They produce a great amount of air while being able to handle higher pressures. It is more efficient and quieter than comparable tubular centrifugal fans. These fans can be used in exhaust, supply or return air applications.

series.name: SMXDK
series.description: Model SMXDK mixed flow fans are inline ducted fans that can be used in exhaust, supply, or return air applications. Mixed flow fans act as a hybrid between axial and centrifugal fans. Meaning, they produce a lot of air such as axial fans, but they can handle higher pressures like centrifugal fans. When these technologies come together, the fan ends up being more efficient and quieter than similar tubular centrifugal fans.

series.name: SMXDK-HT
series.description: SMXDK-HT series is a direct drive mixed flow fan specially designed to maximize the airflow performance by acting as a hybrid between an axial and centrifugal fan. This HT (high temperature) model can provide emergency heat and smoke ventilation in the event of a fire, which can provide valuable time to people exiting or emergency personnel.

series.name: SQB
series.description: SQB square in-line fans, ranging from sizes 7 to 42, deliver efficient airflow up to 24,000 CFM with high static pressure, ideal for space-limited clean air applications. These compact, versatile units are AMCA-certified and UL listed, assuring reliable performance.

series.name: SQD and eSQD
series.description: The SQD square inline duct fan, suitable for tight spaces, comes in sizes 6-15, moving up to 2,800 CFM. eSQD models with EC motors are available in sizes 8, 10, and 12. Their compact design allows for versatile mounting and easy access via removable doors.

series.name: CTB and CTBRHUL
series.description: The Inline Tubular Centrifugal (CTB) series provides a broad selection of sizes and capabilities, with models rated from 300 to 20,000 CFM and up to 2-1/2" static pressure. Designed for commercial and industrial in-line use, these fans are known for quiet, efficient, and reliable air movement. Ideal for various applications like building ventilation, paint spray booths, and kitchen exhausts, the CTB series excels in settings requiring air movement through ducts against moderate static pressure.

series.name: CFD
series.description: The Forward Curved Belt Driven Inline Duct Blowers (CFD) is designed for supply, exhaust or duct return applications. The CFD is an economical fan model designed to run quietly and efficiently in cooling, heating, and ventilating applications.

name: Jet Fans
description: Jet Fans are a pollution control solution that help induce air to a common exhaust point through directed airflow.

series.name: IFFT and IFFTe
series.description: The IFFT and IFFTe centrifugal Jet Fans were designed with relative compactness and efficiency in mind. They are perfect for moving a great deal of air to keep a parking garage safe. The fans induce air flow to move dangerous gases out of enclosed garages and to dedicated ventilation points. The IFFT uses AC motors and the IFFTe uses EC motors. The IFFTe improves the efficiency of the units by using the latest in EC motor technology.

series.name: TJFU
series.description: The TJFU axial jet fans were designed with relative compactness and efficiency in mind. They are perfect for moving a great deal of air to keep a parking garage safe. The fans induce air flow to move dangerous gasses out of enclosed garages and to dedicated ventilation points. Jet fans eliminate the need for ductwork throughout parking areas which reduces installation costs.

series.name: IFAB and IFEB
series.description: The IFAB and IFEB low profile jet fans, designed for compactness and efficiency, are ideal for ventilating parking garages with low ceilings. Their efficient impellers minimize ventilation costs, and their lightweight design ensures easy installation. The IFAB features AC impellers, while the IFEB, equipped with EC impellers, enhances efficiency through advanced EC motor technology.

series.name: 6002, 6002-14B, 6002A and 6002-14A
series.description: Models 6002, 6002-14B, 6002A and 6002-14A offer precision to assure the health and safety to occupants with the tightest possible controls on energy consumption. They are versatile, self-contained dual gas sensors that are network ready for either peer-to-peer (master slave) operation or central control for a smooth integration into new or existing energy management systems.

name: Outside Air Motorized Damper Kits
description: The MDX-ES24VK from S&P allows air to enter dwellings to meet building code and ventilation standards requirements through a motorized damper controlled by a 24V temperature/humidity monitoring control.

series.name: MDX-ES24VK
series.description: The MDX-ES24VK from S&P allows air to enter dwellings to meet building code and ventilation standards requirements through a motorized damper controlled by a 24V temperature/humidity monitoring control. The control can command the central HVAC blower to help distribute fresh air through the existing duct work if necessary.

name: Premium CHOICE Series
description: Premium CHOICE Series ventilation fans give you the flexibility to create the ventilation system you need with our unique plug-&-play technology developed by S&P.

series.name: PC
series.description: The Premium CHOICE XP (PCXP) series addresses indoor air quality (IAQ) in today's tight, compact homes with its seamless, energy-efficient, and quiet performance.

series.name: PCV
series.description: The Premium CHOICE value series (PCV) provides the modular design of PC AC models in more affordable, fully assembled fans or contractor packs, available in sizes PCV50 & PCV80.

series.name: PCD
series.description: The Premium CHOICE DC (PCD) model, with its efficient motor and built-in control boards, enhances indoor air quality by swiftly removing contaminants and moisture, allowing customizable airflow to prevent structural damage and health issues.

series.name: PCLP
series.description: The Premium CHOICE Low Profile Ventilation fans feature ultra-low profile housings suitable for installation in tight ceiling cavities and interstitial spaces where space comes as a premium.

name: reFresh Series
description: The reFresh Series is engineered to meet building and energy codes that call for ASHRAE 62.2 CFM requirements with a design that provides homeowners with the best IAQ solution in an all-in-one unit.

series.name: reFresh Full Size Units
series.description: All-in-one units to introduce fresh air from the outside into the residence. The reFresh series is specifically engineered to meet building and energy codes that call for ASHRAE 62.2 CFM requirements. The reFresh Full Size Units have set speeds at 40, 100, and 170 CFM (Low, Medium, and High).

series.name: reFresh Low Profile
series.description: Low profile, all-in-one units to introduce fresh air from the outside into the residence. The reFresh series is specifically engineered to meet building and energy codes that call for ASHRAE 62.2 CFM requirements. The reFresh Low Profile Units have set speeds at 40, 100, and 140 CFM (Low, Medium, and High).

series.name: reFresh Value
series.description: The reFresh Value Series introduces fresh air from the outside into the residence. The value model is specifically engineered to meet building and energy codes that call for ASHRAE 62.2 (2010), IRC (2012/2015), and IMC (2012/2015) requirements.

name: Roof Propeller Fans
description: The Roof-Mounted Propeller fans are installed on the roofs of buildings to remove or supply air from commercial and industrial facilities economically.

series.name: UBS and UBS-P
series.description: UBS and UBS-P are high capacity roof mounted exhausters rated from 7,000 to 51,000 CFM. They are general ventilation units designed to economically remove large volumes of air, fumes, and vapors from commercial and industrial buildings such as warehouses, manufacturing and assembly plants, chemical plants, foundries and paper mills.

series.name: ARE and ARS
series.description: The AR series, available in four model sizes, offers robust axial exhaust (ARE) or supply (intake) (ARS) performance in a compact, roof-mounted design, suitable for a range of applications including factories, shops, and offices. With a CFM range of 167 to 2,827 and up to 3/4" static pressure, its direct drive design requires minimal maintenance. The series features a sleek, low-profile design with durable all-aluminum housing, catering to light to moderate static pressure environments.

series.name: HRSB and HRSD
series.description: HRSB and HRSD are roof mounted supply fans rated from 4,000 to over 56,000 CFM, with static pressure capability up to 3/4". They are used in a variety of commercial and industrial operations such as warehouses manufacturing plants, equipment and machinery rooms, assembly plants and similar facilities to provide fresh outside air for personal comfort and to reduce negative pressure caused by exhaust systems.

series.name: HREB-C, HREB-P, and HRED-C
series.description: Models HREB-C, HREB-P, and HRED-C are roof-mounted, low-profile exhaust fans rated from 4,000 to over 90,000 CFM with 1” static pressure. Eight sizes from 24-72 inches are available. Available in galvanized or aluminum construction, they are used to exhaust air from a variety of commercial and industrial operations such as manufacturing and assembly plants, warehouses, garages, laundries, and similar buildings.

series.name: UBSRD and UBSRD-P
series.description: Model UBSRD units are high capacity, belt driven roof mounted exhausters rated from 3,700 to 67,000 CFM. The motor and drives are located outside of the exhaust airstream, making these units especially suited for the removal of heated or contaminated air from commercial and industrial buildings or processes where these conditions exist. All models are capable of continuous operation exhausting air to 200°F.

series.name: UBSRD-HT and UBSRD-HT1
series.description: UBSRD-HT and UBSRD-HT1 are available in 24, 30, 36, 42, 48, 54 and 60 inch sizes. Horsepower and CFM range to 52,000 CFM and 10HP. These units have been designed and tested for emergency heat and smoke removal. This design also lends itself to everyday non-emergency high capacity industrial and commercial roof exhaust applications. These fans successfully passed heat tests of 1000°F for fifteen (15) minutes, and 500°F for over four (4) hours by an independent testing agency.

series.name: TUB
series.description: Tubeaxial Upblast Propeller Roof Exhauster Fans (TUB) are designed for high capacity industrial and commercial roof exhaust applications with capacities ranging from 6,210 to 60,116 CFM, with static pressure capability up to 1". The remote drive configuration of the TUB is especially suited for the removal of fumes, vapors, steam, dust, smoke and contaminated or heated air for continuous operation in air temperatures to 200°F. For temperature ratings to 1000°F and/or IRI requirements refer to TUB-HT.

series.name: TUB-HT
series.description: Tubeaxial Upblast Propeller Roof Exhauster for Heat and Smoke Removal Fans (TUB-HT) has been designed and tested for emergency heat, and smoke removal with horsepower's up to 15 HP and CFM up to 57,000. This design also lends itself to normal non-emergency high capacity industrial and commercial roof exhaust applications. TUB-HT's successfully passed heat tests of 1000°F for fifteen (15) minutes, and 500°F for over four (4) hours by an independent testing agency. TUB-HT exceeds I.R.I (Industrial Risk Insurers) guidelines and is UL-793 Listed as "Power Ventilator for Smoke Control Systems."

series.name: UBB and UBX
series.description: UBB and UBX are high capacity roof mounted exhausters rated from 5,900 to 78,000 CFM. They are general ventilation units designed to economically remove large volumes of air, fumes, and vapors from commercial and industrial buildings such as warehouses, manufacturing and assembly plants, distribution centers, chemical plants, foundries and paper mills.

series.name: UBRD
series.description: UBRD units are high capacity belt driven roof mounted exhausters rated from 4,500 to 72,000 CFM. The motor and drives are located outside of the exhaust airstream, making these units especially suited for the removal of heated or contaminated air from commercial and industrial buildings or processes where these conditions exist. All models are capable of continuous operation exhausting air to 200°F.

name: Sidewall Propeller Fans
description: Sidewall Propeller fans are installed on the exterior wall of a building. These types of fans are used to pull air inside the building and expel it outside.

series.name: ACF
series.description: Made of corrosion-resistant galvanized steel, the ACF48 is a durable, value-priced fan with an IP55 motor and sealed ball bearings for diverse applications. It's easily installed via frame holes, with an optional wall box kit available.

series.name: LCE and LCS
series.description: LCE (exhaust) and LCS (supply) are belt-driven propeller fans rated for 3,000 to 40,000 CFM and up to 5/8" w.g. Designed for large volume air movement at low pressures, they're ideal for commercial spaces like warehouses, gyms, poultry houses, and greenhouses.

series.name: GED/eGED and GSD/eGSD
series.description: The GED/eGED and GSD/eGSD Direct Drive Sidewall Propeller Fans, suitable for a variety of environments like factories and churches, offer efficient, low-maintenance operation with quiet performance. Featuring S&P's Electronically Commutated (EC) Motor, these fans combine energy efficiency with ease of maintenance, capable of moving air volumes up to 4,183 CFM. Available in multiple power configurations, they are ideal for cost-effective, controlled ventilation solutions.

series.name: L2E and L2S
series.description: L2E (exhaust) and L2S (supply) are high capacity wall mounted belt driven propeller fans rated from 5,000 to 47,000 CFM, with static pressure capability up to 3/4" w.g. Their primary application is the exhaust of large volumes of ventilation air from commercial and light industrial buildings such as manufacturing and assembly plants, warehouses, parking garages, gymnasiums, equipment rooms, distribution centers and OEM applications.

series.name: L3E and L3S
series.description: L3E (exhaust) and L3S (supply) are high capacity wall mounted belt driven propeller fans rated from 35,000 to 85,000, with static pressure capability up to 1" w.g. Their primary application is the exhaust of large volumes of air at a relatively moderate static pressure from commercial, industrial and agricultural buildings such as manufacturing and assembly plants, warehouses, foundries, mills, boiler rooms and equipment rooms.

series.name: DFE and DFS
series.description: The DFE and DFS Direct Drive Sidewall Propeller Exhaust/Supply Fan feature the maximum efficiency, low maintenance and durable, economical operation resulting from the direct drive design. It is available in exhaust configurations to provide general ventilation for a wide variety of buildings and enclosed areas within buildings. Examples include factories, assembly plants, churches, gymnasiums, garages, jails, machine rooms and many others.

series.name: DDE and DDS
series.description: The DDE and DDS Direct Drive Sidewall Propeller Exhaust/Supply Fan feature the maximum efficiency, low maintenance and durable, economical operation resulting from the direct drive design. It is available in exhaust configurations to provide general ventilation for a wide variety of buildings and enclosed areas within buildings. Examples include factories, assembly plants, churches, gymnasiums, garages, jails, machine rooms and many others.

name: Tubeaxial Fans
description: The Duct-Mounted Tubeaxial fans are designed to supply, exhaust, and boost air in applications with moderate static pressure.

series.name: TDB
series.description: The Tubeaxial line offers the widest range of sizes, horsepower, and performance in the industry. TDB's are high capacity belt drive tubeaxial fans rated from 900 to 75,490 CFM, with static pressure capability up to 1-1/2". They are used to exhaust air from or supply air to commercial and industrial applications, such as general building ventilation, enclosed garages, paint spray booths, heat and smoke ventilation systems and other applications where the air is moved through a duct system against moderate static pressure.

series.name: TDD
series.description: The Tubeaxial line offers the widest range of sizes, horsepower, and performance in the industry. TDD's are high capacity tubeaxial fans rated from 643 to 39,194 CFM, with static pressure capability up to 1-1/4". They are used to exhaust air from or supply air to commercial and industrial applications, such as general building ventilation, enclosed garages, and other applications where the air is moved through a duct system against moderate static pressure.

name: Utility Vent Sets
description: The Roof-Mounted Centrifugal Utility Vent sets are designed to work in medium and high-pressure static pressure applications to exhaust or supply air.

series.name: CM
series.description: The CM Series utility fans are belt-driven for medium to high-pressure commercial and industrial uses. They come with a motor on an adjustable base, v-belt drives, and durable ball bearings. Their easy installation design is cost-effective, and each fan undergoes testing for reliable, low-maintenance operation.
